30:43.816 --> 30:53.527
because their people are constantly dealing with 
students and the public, and so the percentage

30:43.816 --> 30:53.527
there probably is much higher. I think, and on that 
basis I would say astronomers really haven't done

30:55.709 --> 31:03.557
a good job, but I mean, how many astronomers do you 
need to have out there One Carl Sagan is worth

31:04.972 --> 31:09.097
10,000 other astronomers. And so it's kind of hard 
